---
description: Enforce branch naming, commit hygiene, PR discipline, and merge strategy for all repository work.
alwaysApply: true
---

- Never commit directly to protected integration branches; use PR-based flow.
- Branch naming must be `type/short-kebab-name` with allowed prefixes: `feature/`, `fix/`, `hotfix/`, `chore/`.
- Commit messages must be specific, present tense, and scoped to one logical change.
- PRs must include clear change intent and testability context; avoid unrelated mixed-scope PRs.
- Use squash merge for normal feature/fix/chore branches.
- Hotfixes must be synchronized across production and integration branches.

- 🚩 Commit message too vague (`WIP`, `updates`, `fix`, etc.).
- 🚩 Direct push to protected branch.
- 🚩 Stale feature branch not rebased from integration branch.
- 🚩 PR missing description/checklist/test guidance.
- 🚩 Multiple unrelated changes bundled in one commit.
- 🚩 Hotfix merged to production branch but not back-synced.
- ⚠️ Merged feature branch not cleaned up.

See `.cursor/skills/git-workflow/SKILL.md` for full workflow details.
